    <!-- How We Tested -->
    <section>
      <h2>How We Tested These Energy Gummies</h2>

      <div class="tested-box">
        <h3>Our Testing Methodology</h3>
        <p>We purchased all 28 energy gummies with our own money. No brand provided free samples or paid for placement. Our testing protocol spans 8 weeks and evaluates each product across five weighted categories.</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Ingredient Dosing (30% weight)</strong> — We verified the active ingredient content per serving against label claims and compared doses to clinically studied amounts. Products delivering research-backed doses scored highest.</li>
          <li><strong>Energy Effectiveness (25% weight)</strong> — A panel of 10 testers tracked subjective energy levels, alertness, and fatigue across 8 weeks of daily use. Caffeine products were evaluated separately from stimulant-free formulas to ensure fair comparison.</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Testing (20% weight)</strong> — We prioritized products with recognized certifications: USP Verified, NSF Certified, Informed Sport, or equivalent independent lab verification. Uncertified products received lower scores.</li>
          <li><strong>Taste and Texture (15% weight)</strong> — Blind taste testing across our panel. Products were scored on flavor quality, sweetness balance, texture, and aftertaste. Daily compliance depends heavily on taste.</li>
          <li><strong>Value (10% weight)</strong> — We calculated cost per serving, cost per 30-day supply, and cost relative to the active ingredient dose. Products delivering more value per dollar ranked higher.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

